    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290170">
        <title>AIR DRYER AND HEATED DRAIN VALVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f082901001" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G082901001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Air Dryer And Heated Drain Valve Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. AIR DRYER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. KEY SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FUSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HEATED DRAIN VALVE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to the
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825901">Air Dryer And Heated Drain Valve Function Diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>The function of the air dryer is to collect moisture and contaminants before air reaches the first
                reservoir, thus providing moisture free air for the air brake system. The heater in the air dryer
                prevents freeze-up in the purge drain valve during cold weather operation.
            </para>
            <para>The function of the automatic drain valve is to automatically expel accumulated moisture from the air
                tank. The heater in the drain valve prevents freeze-up in the purge drain valve during cold weather
                operation.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
